                    text: "The most frequent issues are high-pressure fuel pump wear, supercharger bearing wear, and intake manifold flap breakage. These are well-documented in GM service bulletins. Fuel pump issues are linked to thermal stress, while supercharger and flap problems stem from material aging under heat. Coolant leaks are design-related and affect pre-2011 units most.",
